cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a convolutional neural network based approach for segmentation and quantification of cardiac contractile functions from cardiac cine MR images. This involves both computer vision (segmentation) and machine learning (multi-task learning) techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.MM) and probabilistic modeling (cs.NE) aspects, which are also relevant sub-categories.
